  "prompt": "Can Home Depot copy a car key with a chip if I provide them a blank key with a chip?",
  "response": "Home Depot offers key copying services, but their capabilities are typically limited to standard keys and some automotive keys. For car keys with a chip (transponder keys), it's best to call your local Home Depot and confirm if they have the necessary equipment to copy and program transponder keys. Not all Home Depot locations have the technology required for this service, and they might refer you to a specialized locksmith or your car dealership for transponder key programming.",
